## 10. Updated unified theorem statement

After Task 1 + Task 2 consolidation, the unified BACL is:

> **BACL (unified, IEEE binary formats, normal + subnormal).**
>
> Let `a, b ∈ 𝔽⁺` in any IEEE 754 binary format with mantissa precision `p` bits (float16: p=11, float32: p=24, float64: p=53). Let `ulp_F(x)` be the format-F ulp.
>
> If `ulp_F(a) ≥ ulp_F(b)`, then `a − b = j · ulp_F(b)` for some integer j ∈ ℤ.
>
> **Verified at:** IEEE binary16, IEEE binary32, IEEE binary64 (normal + subnormal in all cases).
> **Predicted but unverified:** IEEE binary128, bfloat16, and any other binary IEEE format. Proof structure is format-parametric; only ulp value changes.

